 If we have the analytic solution for head or flow in the aquifer due to
 harmonic fluctuating at the boundary, we may solve many related and more
 complex problems by superposition, that is by combining solutions of arbitrary
 frequencies, amplitudes and phase shifts.
 This way, hourly, daily, weekly and seasonal fluctuations may be readily
 combined.
 Examples of applications are tides in groundwater en the depth penetration
 of temperature fluctuations at ground surface.
\end_layout

