\begin_layout Standard
For instance, the water level in Lake Nasser in Egypt has risen by 60 m
 between the mid 1960s, when the dam at Aswan was closed, and the end of
 the 1980s, when the new lake was full.
 This boils down to rise of the lake level of about 3 m/year.
 Just assume that the bordering aquifer is 200 m thick and that it has a
 conductivity 
\begin_inset Formula $k=1\,\mathrm{m/d}$
\end_inset

 and a specific yield 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{y}=0.1$
\end_inset

.
