 Here the water level at the left boundary is suddenly raised by 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 m at 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

 and that at the right side the surface-water level remains unchanged at
 zero.
 The lower picture shows the superposition scheme in which the strip of
 length 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 between points A and B is the one to be analyzed.
 The arrows in the lower picture show where the water level is suddenly
