\begin_inset Formula $kD$
\end_inset

 without worrying about its change due to the drawdown 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 itself.
 However, we can obtain a somewhat more accurate drawdown in case of a water
 table aquifer by taking the change of aquifer thickness into account.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "TheisC1935"
literal "false"

\end_inset

