\begin_layout Standard
In the Hantush case, where the drawdowns will become constant over time,
 the analysis is more difficult.
 The discharges at any distance is obtained from the derivative with respect
 to 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 from the steady-state drawdown will become constant and equal to (see also
