 realistic where the water table is 10 m or more below ground surface.
 In such situations, it may take several months before a recharge pulse
 causes the flow from the unsaturated zone into the saturated zone to increase.
 A thick unsaturated zone causes the recharge arrival in the saturated zone
 to be delayed and somewhat smoothed.
 If this delay and smoothing can be estimated from an unsaturated zone analyses
 of from measurements, it may be included by filtering the recharge time
 series before using it has input for the head simulation.
 Filtering is just a moving averaging procedure, hence a convolution, which
 can be carried out with the same function 
\emph on
lfilter(...)
\emph default
, all we need is a block response that relates the recharge to the flux
 at the bottom of the unsaturated zone.
